WEBVTT

00:02.868 --> 00:04.033
Julia, we should get going.

00:04.033 --> 00:05.334
It's getting kinda late.

00:05.334 --> 00:07.334
I know. I'm sorry.
I'm all messed up.

00:07.334 --> 00:09.000
I can't remember
where I put anything.

00:09.000 --> 00:11.167
So, uh, still no word
from Bailey?

00:11.167 --> 00:12.868
Uh-uh, nothing.

00:12.868 --> 00:14.267
Okay, I think I'm ready.

00:14.267 --> 00:16.767
Book bag, house keys.
I'm wearing clothes.

00:16.767 --> 00:18.167
I called him.

00:19.868 --> 00:21.901
Or I-I tried,
but he wasn't there.

00:21.901 --> 00:22.968
You talked to Callie?

00:22.968 --> 00:25.167
Well, what did she say?

00:25.167 --> 00:27.167
I mean...how's Bailey?
She didn't know.

00:27.167 --> 00:28.534
He didn't come home
last night.

00:28.534 --> 00:30.300
She says it's happened
a couple of times.

00:30.300 --> 00:32.567
He comes home the next day
and never says where he was.

00:32.567 --> 00:34.634
Wait, what do you mean
you called him, Sarah?

00:34.634 --> 00:36.100
I thought we weren't gonna do
that.

00:36.100 --> 00:38.801
Yeah, I know. I know.
But I couldn't help it, okay?

00:38.801 --> 00:40.934
I was worried
and going crazy, so--

00:40.934 --> 00:43.033
Did she say anything else?
Is he going to class?

00:43.033 --> 00:44.901
Maybe we should call him
and just--

00:44.901 --> 00:47.067
Hold on. We said we weren't
gonna do this, right?

00:47.067 --> 00:48.334
It's been four days, Charlie.

00:48.334 --> 00:50.100
Yeah. But that
doesn't change anything.

00:50.100 --> 00:51.801
If we said we won't
call him and see him,

00:51.801 --> 00:53.000
we won't call him and see him.

00:53.000 --> 00:54.100
Well, what does Grace say?

00:54.100 --> 00:55.367
I mean, have you talked to
her?

00:55.367 --> 00:56.767
Can't we call her
at her parents?

00:56.767 --> 00:58.000
Maybe she has an idea.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
Maybe she knows something
that we can do.

01:00.000 --> 01:03.133
She does.
And we're already doing it.

01:03.133 --> 01:04.667
Now, let's stick to it.

01:07.100 --> 01:09.601
But is this all because
of what I said?

01:09.601 --> 01:11.067
CHARLIE:
You were right, Claud.

01:11.067 --> 01:13.634
It's gotta be he quits
or he's out of the family.

01:14.434 --> 01:15.434
But what if I was wrong?

01:15.434 --> 01:17.167
I mean, what it it's like--?

01:17.167 --> 01:19.000
What if it's like
he doesn't have a choice?

01:20.100 --> 01:21.400
'Course he's got a choice.

01:21.400 --> 01:22.901
No. I mean, what if--?

01:22.901 --> 01:25.133
What if he can't help himself?
I mean, he's trying.

01:25.133 --> 01:26.467
And--
And it's like he said,

01:26.467 --> 01:28.234
he's an alcoholic,
and it's in his blood,

01:28.234 --> 01:29.501
and he can't stop drinking.

01:29.501 --> 01:32.200
How's he ever gonna find out
unless he tries?

01:32.200 --> 01:33.801
Huh?

01:33.801 --> 01:36.767
We can't keep
cutting him slack, Claudia,

01:36.767 --> 01:38.801
'cause all he's gonna do
is make more promises

01:38.801 --> 01:40.133
and then break them.

01:43.567 --> 01:45.267
This is what we're doing.

01:45.267 --> 01:47.567
We're drawing a line,
and we're sticking to it.

01:49.400 --> 01:53.334
 <i>[THE BODEANS' "CLOSER TO FIVE"</i>
 <i>PLAYING]</i>

01:54.701 --> 01:57.801
 <i>* Everybody wants to live *</i>

01:57.801 --> 01:59.300
 <i>* Like they wanna live *</i>

01:59.300 --> 02:02.868
 <i>* And everybody wants to love *</i>

02:02.868 --> 02:04.434
 <i>* Like they wanna love *</i>

02:04.434 --> 02:08.400
 <i>* Everybody wants to be *</i>

02:08.400 --> 02:12.868
 <i>* Closer to free-ee-ee-ee *</i>

02:12.868 --> 02:15.534
 <i>* Closer to free *</i>

