02:41.133 --> 02:43.601
That's it. Sorry.
I've gotta go to 160s.

02:43.601 --> 02:45.100
I know. I know.

02:45.100 --> 02:46.100
So it's a forfeit.

02:46.100 --> 02:48.400
Six points
for the visitors.

02:48.400 --> 02:53.000
Um, thanks for spotting us
the time, huh?

02:53.000 --> 02:54.534
It's the divisionals.

02:54.534 --> 02:58.200
You made it this far,
you deserve every chance.

02:58.200 --> 03:01.033
Next weight class,
on the mat.

03:01.033 --> 03:03.734
She's missing the point, because
if I overheard someone saying,

03:03.734 --> 03:05.601
"She's really out there"
about me, I'd be--

03:07.067 --> 03:09.000
[***]

03:11.701 --> 03:13.834
I'd be...

03:30.033 --> 03:31.767
You're back.

03:32.801 --> 03:34.200
Uh-huh.

03:43.400 --> 03:44.901
Oh.

03:56.334 --> 03:58.267
[SIGHING DEEPLY]

04:03.033 --> 04:03.968
Coach.

04:07.601 --> 04:10.234
Hey, coach.

04:13.200 --> 04:15.400
[SIGHS]

04:15.400 --> 04:19.033
I totally--
I totally forgot that--

04:19.033 --> 04:20.534
I mean, not forgot...

04:20.534 --> 04:22.100
What's the matter with you?

04:22.100 --> 04:24.033
Nothing. Uh, nothing.

04:24.033 --> 04:25.667
Then why the hell
weren't you there?

04:25.667 --> 04:28.300
Well, well, that's what
I'm trying to-- To say.

04:28.300 --> 04:29.767
No, no. You know what?

04:29.767 --> 04:31.367
I don't care
what your reasons are.

04:31.367 --> 04:33.200
You're alive,
you should've been there.

04:33.200 --> 04:35.367
I know. I know I should've.

04:35.367 --> 04:38.567
And-- And--
And I feel really bad.

04:39.901 --> 04:42.267
You shoulda
heard those guys today.

04:42.267 --> 04:45.501
You took 'em so far, all the way
to the state divisionals.

04:45.501 --> 04:48.567
They couldn't believe
you pulled a no-show.

04:48.567 --> 04:52.200
You know, last year
the college sent me a form,

04:52.200 --> 04:54.968
saying that I'm vested in
a pension plan

04:54.968 --> 04:57.033
'cause I've been there
15 years.

04:57.033 --> 04:58.300
Heh.

04:58.300 --> 04:59.667
People said, "Oh, that's great.

04:59.667 --> 05:03.100
You'll be taken care of
in your old age."

05:03.100 --> 05:06.968
But all I could think about
is 15 years...

05:06.968 --> 05:10.567
and not one single
divisional trophy.

05:12.100 --> 05:15.100
But this was gonna be my year.

05:15.100 --> 05:16.234
I was sure of it.

05:16.234 --> 05:18.267
See, I had the team.

05:19.634 --> 05:21.667
And they were ready.

05:21.667 --> 05:23.701
They were as fired up
as I was...

05:25.167 --> 05:27.934
'cause we had
an ace in the hole.

05:29.133 --> 05:31.434
We had you.

05:33.200 --> 05:34.567
Coach, can't I--?
No.

05:36.801 --> 05:37.734
No.

05:41.434 --> 05:44.400
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

05:44.400 --> 05:45.400
[SIGHS]

05:45.400 --> 05:46.834
[CAR STARTS]

05:48.300 --> 05:51.234
You think it was like this
with Mom and Dad?

05:51.234 --> 05:53.534
This stuff with Bailey?

05:53.534 --> 05:55.801
I don't know, Claud.

05:55.801 --> 05:58.434
I mean, when she told him
to quit--

05:58.434 --> 06:00.133
Do you think
he was like Bailey?

06:00.133 --> 06:03.467
I mean, do you think
he made it this hard?

06:03.467 --> 06:06.267
Maybe. Who knows?

06:06.267 --> 06:07.834
I mean, if she
was ready to leave him,

06:07.834 --> 06:10.467
he must have been pretty bad.

06:12.834 --> 06:16.267
And Bailey, he said all those
awful things to us.

06:16.267 --> 06:18.901
Do you think Dad was like that
with her?

06:18.901 --> 06:21.400
I mean, do you think
he talked to her like that?

06:21.400 --> 06:22.634
I don't remember.

06:22.634 --> 06:24.667
Did he threaten her,
or--?

06:24.667 --> 06:26.033
Or--? Or hit her?

06:27.567 --> 06:29.133
No way.

06:29.133 --> 06:30.734
Why are you--?
Bailey shoved you,

06:30.734 --> 06:32.300
Charlie, and he tried
to hit you.

06:32.300 --> 06:35.300
And if Dad was ever drunk
like Bailey...

06:35.300 --> 06:39.334
Do you remember when
you were a kid, you know,

06:39.334 --> 06:40.934
I mean, did you ever
hear anything?

06:40.934 --> 06:42.300
Claud.

06:42.300 --> 06:44.067
It was a long time ago.

06:44.067 --> 06:45.634
And really, I don't--
I don't get why

06:45.634 --> 06:47.100
you need
to know all this stuff.

06:47.100 --> 06:48.234
I just do.

06:48.234 --> 06:50.100
And I know you remember
something, Charlie,

06:50.100 --> 06:52.601
'cause you remember those drives
with Mom to pick up his car,

06:52.601 --> 06:54.767
and you remembered her
being mad at him.

06:54.767 --> 06:56.167
Yeah,
but that's all I remember.

06:56.167 --> 06:57.501
But that can't be everything.

06:57.501 --> 06:59.701
I mean, there's--
There's gotta be something.

07:01.067 --> 07:03.801
No, Claud, there isn't.

07:03.801 --> 07:05.067
I'm sorry.

07:10.634 --> 07:12.501
Last night Claudia
slept in the living room

07:12.501 --> 07:14.367
'cause she was afraid
she'd miss the phone,

07:14.367 --> 07:16.367
in case Bailey called to say,
"I made a mistake.

07:16.367 --> 07:18.033
I wanna stop drinking.
Take me back."

07:18.033 --> 07:21.033
And yesterday, I'm driving home
from school and--

07:21.033 --> 07:22.834
And I'm kind of
in Bailey's neighborhood,

07:22.834 --> 07:24.901
so I decide to swing by
and see if his car is there,

07:24.901 --> 07:26.100
which it it wasn't.

07:26.100 --> 07:28.000
But you know whose was?
Charlie's.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.033
Charlie is sitting there like me
hoping to see Bailey.

07:34.267 --> 07:36.734
Hey, are you limping?

07:36.734 --> 07:37.734
No. No, not really.

07:37.734 --> 07:38.934
I just kind of get stiff

07:38.934 --> 07:40.767
whenever I'm off of it
for a little while.

07:42.300 --> 07:44.033
Ungh.
What about Bailey's roommate?

07:44.033 --> 07:45.667
What does she say?
Griffin, you are.

07:45.667 --> 07:46.634
You're limping.

07:47.934 --> 07:50.467
I just had a little fall
on the boat.

07:50.467 --> 07:52.667
A--? A fall? When was this?

07:52.667 --> 07:54.200
A couple months ago.

07:54.200 --> 07:56.367
And--?
And you're still limping?

07:56.367 --> 07:58.267
There's some scar tissue
in the knee joint.

07:58.267 --> 07:59.767
Well, why didn't
you say anything?

07:59.767 --> 08:01.367
I mean, this is pretty major.

08:01.367 --> 08:02.734
I don't know.

08:04.534 --> 08:06.801
I guess I was just afraid
that you'd be disappointed.

08:06.801 --> 08:09.534
What? D-disappointed because
you hurt your knee?

08:09.534 --> 08:10.801
No.

08:13.334 --> 08:17.033
Just I-I-I can't do
that kind of work anymore,

08:17.033 --> 08:18.634
so...

08:18.634 --> 08:20.067
So they kinda fired me.

08:20.067 --> 08:21.400
S-o...?

08:21.400 --> 08:23.400
So...

08:23.400 --> 08:25.267
So I wanted to come back
with all that stuff,

08:25.267 --> 08:27.634
you know, like you said.

08:27.634 --> 08:30.000
A job and a--
And a purpose.

08:30.000 --> 08:34.333
Griffin, I really don't care
about that stuff anymore.

08:34.333 --> 08:37.167
Last time I saw you, you
practically had a 20-year plan.

08:37.167 --> 08:41.167
Yeah. Well, lately I haven't
been planning so far in advance.

08:41.167 --> 08:44.667
What? What, like you know how
many kids you're gonna have,

08:44.667 --> 08:46.200
you just haven't named 'em yet?

08:46.200 --> 08:50.033
No. No. Nothing like that.

08:50.033 --> 08:52.968
In fact, right now
I think I'd be happy

08:52.968 --> 08:56.467
just to plan on
spending some time with you.

08:56.467 --> 08:58.467
 <i>* Help me *</i>

08:58.467 --> 09:01.100
 <i>* Outrun it inside my head *</i>

09:01.100 --> 09:05.033
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
OVER STEREO]

09:12.167 --> 09:13.968
CALLIE:
There's no messages.

09:13.968 --> 09:15.701
Were you wondering
if they called?

09:15.701 --> 09:16.767
Who?

09:16.767 --> 09:18.567
Your family.

09:18.567 --> 09:21.300
My family? My family?

09:21.300 --> 09:23.701
Why--?
I don't care if they called.

09:23.701 --> 09:24.834
'Cause they didn't.

09:24.834 --> 09:26.734
I said, I don't care.

09:26.734 --> 09:29.734
I was expecting
a call from someone else.

09:29.734 --> 09:31.467
From the coach.

09:31.467 --> 09:32.801
Oh, uh-huh.

09:32.801 --> 09:35.267
Why would I wanna
hear from them?

09:35.267 --> 09:39.267
All they wanna do is send me off
to Betty Ford clinic.

09:40.667 --> 09:41.868
[SIGHS]

09:41.868 --> 09:44.334
So where was the party?

09:44.334 --> 09:45.501
What party?

09:46.400 --> 09:48.234
Come on, Bailey...

09:49.200 --> 09:50.367
No party.

09:50.367 --> 09:52.934
I was...

09:52.934 --> 09:56.567
I was just celebrating
because...

09:56.567 --> 09:58.834
Because today--

09:58.834 --> 10:00.834
And I know this is starting
to sound a little bit

10:00.834 --> 10:03.033
monotonous 'cause it happens
just about every day.

10:04.634 --> 10:06.501
--I won another match.

10:06.501 --> 10:10.434
And so, of course, I had to
go celebrate with the guys.

10:10.434 --> 10:12.267
Yeah.

10:13.501 --> 10:15.634
Well, congratulations.

10:20.000 --> 10:23.200
 <i>* Beside the sidewalks *</i>

10:23.200 --> 10:28.167
 <i>* With your tails</i>
 <i>Hanging out *</i>

10:28.167 --> 10:32.868
 <i>* Check if her eyes</i>
 <i>Are still... *</i>

10:32.868 --> 10:34.801
So, ungh,

10:34.801 --> 10:36.734
what's going on with you?

10:36.734 --> 10:38.234
Tell me every little thing.

10:38.234 --> 10:39.667
Bailey, not now.
Okay?

10:39.667 --> 10:41.767
I gotta work.

10:41.767 --> 10:43.167
Come on.

10:43.167 --> 10:45.501
Not now. Okay?

10:45.501 --> 10:46.434
Come on.

10:47.968 --> 10:50.167
Bailey, please, please.

10:51.367 --> 10:52.601
Bailey...

10:52.601 --> 10:53.601
What about now?

10:53.601 --> 10:54.868
I said no!

10:56.334 --> 10:59.267
God, what's your problem?

10:59.267 --> 11:00.968
I was just trying to
get you in the mood.

11:00.968 --> 11:03.267
Oh, this is supposed to be
a turn-on?

11:03.267 --> 11:05.834
You crawl into bed wasted
and slobber all over me?

11:05.834 --> 11:08.467
Oh, so it's okay
when you're buzzed too,

11:08.467 --> 11:11.033
but let me be a couple of drinks
ahead and all of a sudden

11:11.033 --> 11:13.634
you rediscover
your long-lost virginity?

11:14.534 --> 11:15.834
Huh?

11:16.901 --> 11:18.834
You know what?

11:18.834 --> 11:20.868
They are right about you.

11:20.868 --> 11:21.934
You got a problem.

11:29.200 --> 11:33.634
I knew your mother, Claudia.
I-I really didn't know Nick.

11:33.634 --> 11:35.968
But you must have seen him.

11:35.968 --> 11:39.834
I mean, like after concerts
or at parties or whatever.

11:39.834 --> 11:41.767
Briefly, maybe, but...

11:41.767 --> 11:43.467
She must have said something.

11:43.467 --> 11:45.234
You-- You guys
must have talked.

11:45.234 --> 11:46.968
I mean, come on,
you were partners.

11:46.968 --> 11:48.901
You know, I-I-I really
don't remember.

11:48.901 --> 11:51.467
Try, Avery, please.

11:51.467 --> 11:53.133
What did she say?

11:53.133 --> 11:55.467
It was long time ago, Claudia.

11:55.467 --> 11:56.934
I don't wanna hear that anymore.

11:56.934 --> 11:59.200
Okay? I mean, that-- That's
just what Charlie says.

11:59.200 --> 12:01.033
Claudia, please,
I really don't--

12:01.033 --> 12:02.601
No.

12:03.734 --> 12:06.133
Because I know
what you're doing.

12:06.133 --> 12:07.868
You're trying to protect me.

12:07.868 --> 12:09.868
But see,

12:09.868 --> 12:11.033
you're not.

12:12.434 --> 12:15.701
How does it help you to think
bad things about your father?

12:17.400 --> 12:20.367
I don't wanna think
bad things, Avery.

12:20.367 --> 12:24.467
I wanna think good things,

12:24.467 --> 12:26.968
but I can't.

12:26.968 --> 12:30.834
Because whenever I try,
whenever I remember him,

12:30.834 --> 12:34.868
like, posing us for one of those
stupid Christmas cards

12:34.868 --> 12:38.133
in-- In a human pyramid
or something, it just...

12:38.133 --> 12:39.601
It seems fake.

12:39.601 --> 12:43.667
Like I'm remembering something
the way he wanted me to.

12:43.667 --> 12:46.100
But not how it really was.

12:48.534 --> 12:50.067
He drank too much, Claudia.

12:50.067 --> 12:51.968
What more do you need to know?

12:51.968 --> 12:54.067
I wanna know what he was like.

12:55.667 --> 12:58.200
What he was really like.

13:02.200 --> 13:04.868
Wait. This is, like,
glued this way?

13:04.868 --> 13:08.200
I mean,
it's, uh, 16 bucks a night.

13:08.200 --> 13:09.667
I mean, I talked him down
from 20.

13:09.667 --> 13:13.567
Oh, you shoulda kept talking.

13:13.567 --> 13:16.033
I mean, you try to find a room
this cheap in San Francisco.

13:16.033 --> 13:17.400
No thanks...

13:19.501 --> 13:20.634
Ugh.

13:22.033 --> 13:24.434
I'm not saying...

13:24.434 --> 13:26.634
I just think
you could you better.

13:26.634 --> 13:28.834
Not without a job,
I can't.

13:28.834 --> 13:30.868
I haven't even had time
to start looking.

13:30.868 --> 13:32.133
I know.

13:32.133 --> 13:35.067
But m-maybe that's not
the only way.

13:35.067 --> 13:37.501
Getting a-- A job, I mean.

13:37.501 --> 13:41.434
I don't understand what--
Suggesting I knock over a bank?

13:41.434 --> 13:43.100
No. No.

13:43.100 --> 13:45.868
I-I was just thinking about
that thing on-- On the boat.

13:45.868 --> 13:48.267
You know, the accident
with your knee,

13:48.267 --> 13:50.501
'cause that was their fault.

13:50.501 --> 13:52.434
Right?
D-didn't you say that?

13:52.434 --> 13:54.634
Yeah, it was completely against
union regulations.

13:54.634 --> 13:56.634
They should have never
sent me up that bulkhead

13:56.634 --> 13:59.033
without the bosun's rating.
Right.

13:59.033 --> 14:01.367
So it just seems to me
that they owe you something.

14:01.367 --> 14:05.234
Heh. Probably seems
a little different to them.

14:05.234 --> 14:07.634
Yeah. Well...

14:08.334 --> 14:10.100
maybe you should sue.

14:11.400 --> 14:12.968
What do you mean, sue?

14:12.968 --> 14:15.434
You mean, like--?
You mean, like go to court sue?

14:15.434 --> 14:17.601
Yeah. Griffin,
i-it's a good idea.

14:17.601 --> 14:18.767
'Cause-- 'Cause listen.

14:18.767 --> 14:21.801
Listen, I-I could help you
find a good lawyer,

14:21.801 --> 14:23.901
and they could get you whatever
money they owe you.

14:23.901 --> 14:26.100
And-- And you could
buy yourself some time.

14:27.234 --> 14:28.567
Time for what?

14:28.567 --> 14:31.701
Time to find a job that
you're really psyched about,

14:31.701 --> 14:33.400
not just the first one
that comes along,

14:33.400 --> 14:35.634
but one you'd wanna
stick around for.

14:35.634 --> 14:37.634
So you just got this
all figured out, don't you?

14:37.634 --> 14:39.434
Or maybe you could
get enough money so that

14:39.434 --> 14:41.667
you could take a break
before you started working.

14:41.667 --> 14:43.734
You know, do something fun,
like-- Like travel.

14:43.734 --> 14:46.467
Go someplace that you didn't
see enough of on the boat.

14:46.467 --> 14:49.801
Some place that you'd like
to show a friend.

14:50.834 --> 14:51.834
Friend?

14:53.634 --> 14:55.634
[***]

14:55.634 --> 15:00.234
I wanna get out of here,
Griffin, don't you?

15:00.234 --> 15:01.367
I just got here.

15:01.367 --> 15:05.534
No. I wanna go someplace
great with you.

15:05.534 --> 15:08.200
I want you to take me
someplace great.

15:11.334 --> 15:15.067
You-- You want me to, uh...

15:17.000 --> 15:18.734
Wow.

15:21.033 --> 15:22.601
Uh, okay.

15:25.200 --> 15:27.100
So, what are you doing here?

15:27.100 --> 15:28.234
Picking up Owen.

15:28.234 --> 15:29.501
Owen? Well, he's not here.

15:29.501 --> 15:31.167
He was picked up already.

15:31.167 --> 15:32.968
He--? What--? What are you
talking about?

15:32.968 --> 15:33.968
Who picked him up?

15:33.968 --> 15:35.033
Uh, your brother Bailey.

15:35.968 --> 15:37.734
Bailey?

15:37.734 --> 15:39.434
Bailey is your brother,
isn't he?

15:39.434 --> 15:41.634
Yes. Yeah. But...

15:43.567 --> 15:44.968
How did he seem?

15:44.968 --> 15:47.267
Who, Bailey? Fine.

15:47.267 --> 15:49.167
Actually, they had
a lot of fun.

15:49.167 --> 15:50.901
Bailey was throwing Owen
up in the air,

15:50.901 --> 15:51.934
they were playing tag.

15:51.934 --> 15:53.200
They both were in hysterics.

15:53.200 --> 15:55.067
There you go, sweetie.
Right there.

15:55.067 --> 15:57.300
So was he, um...?

15:57.801 --> 15:58.734
What?

16:00.067 --> 16:01.367
Nothing.

16:01.367 --> 16:04.300
Nothing.

16:04.300 --> 16:06.868
Uh, if he ever comes
to pick up Owen again...

16:06.868 --> 16:07.968
What?

16:09.300 --> 16:10.234
Nothing.

16:21.033 --> 16:22.467
No more cotton candy?

16:22.467 --> 16:24.200
No.
You sure?

16:24.200 --> 16:27.400
As soon as you get home,
those scrooges will have you

16:27.400 --> 16:29.934
back on spinach
and Brussels sprouts.

16:29.934 --> 16:32.434
I feel sick.

16:32.434 --> 16:33.434
Okay.

16:33.434 --> 16:35.133
That's how I know when to quit.

16:36.067 --> 16:37.667
Ah, no wonder you feel gross.

16:37.667 --> 16:40.868
This stuff's all over you
like alien pod slime.

16:46.767 --> 16:49.334
I'm not saying that they-- They
don't mean well or anything,

16:49.334 --> 16:53.767
you know, I'm just saying
you gotta be pretty damn--

16:53.767 --> 16:56.567
Darn-- Pretty darn close
to perfect

16:56.567 --> 16:58.734
to make those people happy.

16:58.734 --> 17:00.133
You know?

17:01.467 --> 17:03.968
Thank God you don't know
what I'm talking about.

17:03.968 --> 17:05.666
We need to get you
to the bathroom.

17:05.666 --> 17:07.601
These Handi Wipes
only do an inch at a time.

17:08.567 --> 17:09.968
Here we go.

17:09.968 --> 17:11.467
[GRUNTS]

17:11.467 --> 17:12.400
Okay.

17:16.467 --> 17:17.701
Who's your favorite brother?

17:18.901 --> 17:20.767
Bailey, stupid.

17:20.767 --> 17:22.733
Bailey's stupid.

17:22.733 --> 17:24.534
Okay. We're gonna have to
work on that.

17:24.534 --> 17:25.800
Come on.
[GIGGLING]

17:25.800 --> 17:28.267
[BAILEY GRUNTS]

17:28.267 --> 17:32.501
The facts of this case are very
compelling, Gavin, I must admit.

17:32.501 --> 17:35.367
But you are a David
going up against

17:35.367 --> 17:37.400
a very greedy
corporate Godzilla.

17:37.400 --> 17:39.801
So to think you can fight
the good fight without stooping

17:39.801 --> 17:42.501
to the level of your enemy,
it's just plain naive.

17:42.501 --> 17:45.067
What are you saying
exactly?

17:45.067 --> 17:47.534
Well, just that liability law's
a very tricky things,

17:47.534 --> 17:51.167
and in making a case, some
facts are better than others.

17:51.167 --> 17:52.667
Right.

17:52.667 --> 17:57.234
But Griffin is actually hurt,
and it is actually their fault.

17:57.234 --> 17:59.400
So, what other facts
do you need?

17:59.400 --> 18:00.968
LAWYER:
I'm just reminding you

18:00.968 --> 18:05.033
that justice is blind,
and sometimes she misses things.

18:05.033 --> 18:06.868
So let them see my limp?

18:06.868 --> 18:08.968
Your boyfriend is very smart.
[PHONE RINGS]

18:08.968 --> 18:10.100
Uh-huh.

18:10.100 --> 18:12.567
Hang on.
MAN: <i>Where the hell were you?</i>

18:12.567 --> 18:14.634
 <i>You know how long I've been</i>
 <i>rotting in this jail?</i>

18:14.634 --> 18:17.267
Sal, hold on.
There's no need to shout.

18:17.267 --> 18:18.601
Oh, yeah?

18:18.601 --> 18:20.501
Well, sometimes jail
is good for people.

18:20.501 --> 18:23.367
It teaches them things,
like not to pass

18:23.367 --> 18:25.434
bad paper to their
very own lawyers.

18:25.434 --> 18:27.601
SAL:
 <i>What are you talking about?</i>

18:27.601 --> 18:28.901
Let me take this next door.

18:30.367 --> 18:33.534
Gavin, work on that limp.
Heh-heh-heh!

18:35.267 --> 18:39.434
Oh, my God.
This guy is unbelievable.

18:39.434 --> 18:41.033
Do you think
we should sneak out now,

18:41.033 --> 18:43.067
or would he sue us for that?

18:43.067 --> 18:45.534
What are you talking about?
You don't like Arnie?

18:45.534 --> 18:48.167
Griffin, he's cute,
but you need a lawyer.

18:48.167 --> 18:50.634
You saw all those clippings.
He's won tons of cases.

18:50.634 --> 18:54.667
Do you think a judge is
actually gonna believe this guy?

18:54.667 --> 18:56.267
I feel like
he's selling me a used car.

18:56.267 --> 18:58.734
I feel like he's selling me
my used car.

19:00.467 --> 19:02.267
Well, I'm sorry
that you feel that way.

19:02.267 --> 19:03.934
But I already promised Arnie
this case.

19:03.934 --> 19:05.734
I can't go back on my word.

19:05.734 --> 19:08.400
Griffin, this is serious.

19:08.400 --> 19:10.000
This could cost you
a lot of money,

19:10.000 --> 19:11.667
and it's money you need.

19:11.667 --> 19:14.100
It could make a lot of things
possible for you.

19:14.100 --> 19:16.334
You know, I hate
when you do this,

19:16.334 --> 19:18.067
because it's the same deal
every time.

19:18.067 --> 19:19.968
You know, g-give Griffin
something to do,

19:19.968 --> 19:22.467
and you can count on it,
he's gonna screw it up.

19:22.467 --> 19:23.834
He always does.

19:23.834 --> 19:26.300
I-I'm not talking about you.
I'm talking about him.

19:26.300 --> 19:27.367
He's a joke.

19:27.367 --> 19:29.133
He's not a joke.

19:29.133 --> 19:30.901
I mean, maybe he's not
some fancy lawyer,

19:30.901 --> 19:33.334
but I can't afford that.

19:33.334 --> 19:34.501
He's a bulldog.

19:34.501 --> 19:36.534
You know, sometimes
that's what you need.

19:36.534 --> 19:38.000
[TAPPING ON WINDOW]

19:40.334 --> 19:43.534
Griffin, please tell me
you're not gonna hire this guy.

19:43.534 --> 19:46.868
Please tell me this
isn't who we're depending on.

19:49.901 --> 19:51.267
[DOOR OPENS]

19:52.434 --> 19:53.834
[DOOR CLOSES]

19:54.868 --> 19:55.868
Hey.

19:55.868 --> 19:58.567
Hey, what are you doing here?

19:58.567 --> 19:59.601
Did he call?

20:00.801 --> 20:01.801
[SIGHS]

20:01.801 --> 20:04.734
What? What happened?

20:04.734 --> 20:07.467
Bailey picked up Owen from
daycare without telling anyone,

20:07.467 --> 20:08.734
and they're not back yet.

20:08.734 --> 20:10.067
And now it's dark out.

20:10.067 --> 20:11.734
Well, how long
have they been gone?

20:11.734 --> 20:12.801
Four hours.

20:12.801 --> 20:14.534
He picked up Owen
four hours ago.

20:14.534 --> 20:16.067
And--? And was he drinking?

20:16.067 --> 20:17.567
Did they say
anything about that?

20:17.567 --> 20:19.400
They said he was all hyped-up
with the kids.

20:19.400 --> 20:20.567
So who knows?

20:20.567 --> 20:22.334
A-and he definitely
hasn't called?

20:22.334 --> 20:25.334
You checked the messages
at the restaurant, right?

20:25.334 --> 20:26.334
I check five times.

20:26.334 --> 20:28.834
I called the daycare center too.
Nothing.

20:28.834 --> 20:30.534
Oh, my God, what if
they had an accident?

20:30.534 --> 20:32.133
We already called
all the hospitals.

20:32.133 --> 20:33.334
And what about the police?

20:33.334 --> 20:36.234
No.
But we gotta do that.

20:36.234 --> 20:37.868
No, no, no, no. Wait.
I mean, we can't.

20:37.868 --> 20:40.467
I mean, what--? What if they
pull Bailey over and he's drunk?

20:40.467 --> 20:44.234
No. You know what?
You should call. You should.

20:44.234 --> 20:46.634
I mean, besides, what's
the worst thing that can happen?

20:46.634 --> 20:48.934
She's right. I mean,
so what if he loses his license?

20:48.934 --> 20:50.634
I wanna find Owen.

20:52.434 --> 20:54.033
[***]

21:00.801 --> 21:03.834
Hello? Yes. Uh...

21:03.834 --> 21:05.701
No, it's not an emergency.

21:05.701 --> 21:09.300
Except, um, I need
to find my brother.

21:09.300 --> 21:11.834
He kinda disappeared,
and he's with my other brother,

21:11.834 --> 21:14.167
and I'm worried.

21:14.167 --> 21:17.934
I don't know if I can trust him
to drive 'cause he might be,

21:17.934 --> 21:20.033
um...

21:20.033 --> 21:21.868
Can you just...?

21:21.868 --> 21:23.601
Can you just help me find him?

21:25.133 --> 21:28.334
No! Bailey! Bailey!

21:28.334 --> 21:30.167
Bailey, stop!
Hang on, buddy.

21:30.167 --> 21:31.934
Few more yards.

21:31.934 --> 21:32.934
Touchdown.

21:32.934 --> 21:34.434
Put me down!

21:39.801 --> 21:42.200
Come on, buddy.

21:42.200 --> 21:44.267
That's the sign of a good ride,

21:44.267 --> 21:45.934
when you can't wait
for it to end.

21:56.100 --> 21:57.634
[CLAUDIA SIGHS]

22:03.801 --> 22:06.133
He used to do this too.

22:06.133 --> 22:07.234
Who?

22:07.234 --> 22:09.467
Dad.

22:09.467 --> 22:11.901
He used to take
these fishing trips,

22:11.901 --> 22:13.801
back when he was drinking.

22:13.801 --> 22:16.701
This one time he was supposed to
come back on a Sunday.

22:16.701 --> 22:19.467
And it was already Tuesday,
and she hadn't heard a word.

22:19.467 --> 22:21.367
So, I mean, she really
started freaking,

22:21.367 --> 22:23.801
like-- Like calling the cops
and everything.

22:23.801 --> 22:27.234
And when he finally got back,
he was drunk.

22:27.234 --> 22:30.634
And instead of saying
he was sorry,

22:30.634 --> 22:31.701
he yelled at her.

22:31.701 --> 22:33.434
Who told you this?

22:35.100 --> 22:36.100
Avery.

22:37.267 --> 22:38.634
He said Dad yelled at her

22:38.634 --> 22:41.400
for making a big deal
out of him being late.

22:41.400 --> 22:43.200
I mean, he got really mad at her

22:43.200 --> 22:46.334
for making him look
irresponsible to people.

22:48.200 --> 22:50.400
Just in case you think
this is bad,

22:50.400 --> 22:52.801
it gets worse.
You went to see Avery?

22:54.734 --> 22:55.734
Why?

22:55.734 --> 22:57.334
Because I wanted to know.

22:59.234 --> 23:01.200
And he told me everything.

23:01.200 --> 23:02.501
BAILEY:
Arms out. Here you go.

23:02.501 --> 23:04.467
He's here. Bailey's here.

23:06.234 --> 23:08.367
[IMITATING MOTOR]

23:08.367 --> 23:10.434
Just what the hell
do you think you're doing?

23:10.434 --> 23:11.701
Excuse me?
Come here, Owen.

23:11.701 --> 23:13.300
Are you okay?
Look at me.

23:13.300 --> 23:15.634
What's the matter with you?
Of course he's okay.

23:15.634 --> 23:17.734
JULIA:
Let's get you ready for dinner.

23:17.734 --> 23:19.734
Where the hell have you been?

23:19.734 --> 23:21.367
Where the hell have you been?!

23:21.367 --> 23:22.667
Where the hell have I been?

23:22.667 --> 23:24.634
I took Owen for a ride.

23:24.634 --> 23:26.434
What the hell
is so "the hell" about it?

23:26.434 --> 23:28.834
You took him from daycare
without telling anybody,

23:28.834 --> 23:30.734
and then you kept him all day
without calling?

23:30.734 --> 23:33.434
BAILEY:
I spent the afternoon with my
little brother. Big deal.

23:33.434 --> 23:35.834
I do it all the time.
No, you don't!

23:35.834 --> 23:37.934
The last couple months you've
been totally AWOL.

23:37.934 --> 23:40.167
I'm making up for lost time.
What's wrong with that?

23:40.167 --> 23:42.634
Because we had no way
of knowing if--

23:42.634 --> 23:43.901
How are we supposed to know--?

23:43.901 --> 23:45.667
If I was drunk?

23:45.667 --> 23:48.634
Is that what this is about?

23:48.634 --> 23:50.934
You--? You thought
that I'd be wasted, right?

23:50.934 --> 23:52.834
You thought that
I would drive around wasted

23:52.834 --> 23:54.501
and get Owen killed.

23:54.501 --> 23:56.634
Well, are you?

23:58.067 --> 24:00.400
Oh, that's really sweet.

24:00.400 --> 24:02.901
Just when I thought my family
couldn't love me any less.

24:02.901 --> 24:04.300
Have you had anything to drink?

24:04.300 --> 24:05.467
No, I haven't.

24:05.467 --> 24:06.834
Let me smell your breath.

24:06.834 --> 24:07.834
Get away from me.

24:11.834 --> 24:12.968
You have.

24:12.968 --> 24:14.767
You've been drinking.

24:14.767 --> 24:16.734
I had a beer,
Charlie, one beer.

24:16.734 --> 24:20.033
You drank and you drove with
your little brother in the car!

24:20.033 --> 24:21.534
I am completely sober! Okay?

24:21.534 --> 24:23.868
You wanna give me a blood test?
I don't believe you!

24:23.868 --> 24:25.667
Somebody oughta--

24:25.667 --> 24:27.000
Well, come on! Go on!

24:28.467 --> 24:29.834
No, Charlie! No, Charlie!

24:29.834 --> 24:32.634
Charlie, Charlie, stop it!
Please, stop!

24:32.634 --> 24:34.701
Now! Stop it!

24:35.334 --> 24:37.200
[PANTING]

24:37.200 --> 24:39.167
Bailey...

24:42.467 --> 24:44.667
Just stay away from Owen,
you hear me?!

24:44.667 --> 24:46.901
Wreck your own life,
but you're not gonna hurt him!

24:46.901 --> 24:48.868
He's my brother.
No, he's not!

24:53.167 --> 24:55.200
BAILEY:
I can't believe...

24:55.200 --> 24:56.467
you people...

25:00.701 --> 25:03.000
Bailey.

25:03.000 --> 25:04.701
We gotta go after him,
right?

25:06.334 --> 25:08.968
I mean, obviously,
this isn't working.

25:08.968 --> 25:10.934
He isn't gonna learn anything
like this.

25:10.934 --> 25:12.901
He's been drinking,
and now he's gonna drive,

25:12.901 --> 25:15.767
and we've got to
do something, right?

25:18.801 --> 25:20.267
Right?

25:20.267 --> 25:22.968
 <i>* You're on the run *</i>

25:22.968 --> 25:25.267
 <i>* From your parents</i>
 <i>And the law *</i>

25:25.267 --> 25:27.601
[TIRES SQUEALING]

25:30.534 --> 25:32.801
 <i>* I didn't see it then *</i>

25:32.801 --> 25:36.133
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
 <i>* That I was your getaway *</i>

25:36.133 --> 25:38.167
 <i>* Car *</i>

25:40.634 --> 25:43.968
 <i>* And I didn't have</i>
 <i>The bottle *</i>

25:43.968 --> 25:47.067
 <i>* Yet you drank down</i>
 <i>All my... *</i>

25:47.067 --> 25:48.000
Hey.

25:49.634 --> 25:52.100
If I'd known you were coming,
I'd have fixed the good cereal.

25:53.133 --> 25:55.901
Julia, what's wrong?

25:57.100 --> 25:58.767
Is it Bailey?

25:58.767 --> 26:00.801
[CRYING]

26:01.968 --> 26:04.200
You're gonna be okay,
all right?

26:04.200 --> 26:05.534
You're gonna be all right.

26:05.534 --> 26:07.033
I'm here. Okay?

26:07.033 --> 26:10.567
 <i>* Always believed you *</i>

26:10.567 --> 26:13.434
 <i>* When you said that you... *</i>

26:13.434 --> 26:14.767
I'm right here.

26:18.434 --> 26:24.901
 <i>* But to you the Earth</i>
 <i>Was never close enough *</i>

26:32.100 --> 26:35.133
 <i>* And I like the view *</i>

26:35.133 --> 26:37.734
 <i>* Far from the light *</i>

26:37.734 --> 26:40.601
 <i>* I don't need to get close *</i>

26:40.601 --> 26:44.534
 <i>* To start feeling alive *</i>

26:46.067 --> 26:51.434
 <i>* And my love is running *</i>

26:51.434 --> 26:54.667
 <i>* When my love is running *</i>

26:54.667 --> 26:56.334
Are you sure?

26:58.467 --> 26:59.434
Yeah.

27:11.000 --> 27:13.501
Charlie, are you all right?
On the phone you sounded like--

27:13.501 --> 27:15.000
I'd just like to know
why you did it.

27:15.000 --> 27:16.334
Sorry?

27:16.334 --> 27:17.734
[DOOR CLOSES]

27:20.567 --> 27:22.934
Why'd you tell Claudia
all that stuff about our father?

27:22.934 --> 27:24.634
Well, she came in all upset,
and I just--

27:24.634 --> 27:26.033
Well, exactly. Exactly.

27:26.033 --> 27:27.167
She's upset.

27:27.167 --> 27:29.467
She's upset about drinking
in our family.

27:29.467 --> 27:32.734
You tell her that her father's
some kind of abusive drunk?

27:32.734 --> 27:33.734
Why would you do that?

27:33.734 --> 27:34.801
Charlie, wait. That's--

27:34.801 --> 27:36.334
Because this alcoholism thing,

27:36.334 --> 27:37.734
the way it works, she'll think

27:37.734 --> 27:40.133
that whatever happened to Dad
is gonna happen to Bailey.

27:40.133 --> 27:42.467
She asked me what I remembered.
All I told her--

27:42.467 --> 27:45.367
And the fact of the matter is,
is that Dad was never that bad.

27:45.367 --> 27:47.267
I remember him from back then
too, you know,

27:47.267 --> 27:50.100
and I don't remember any of
the stuff that you told Claudia.

27:50.968 --> 27:53.834
I mean, he drank too much. Sure.

27:53.834 --> 27:55.534
And there was some yelling,
definitely.

27:55.534 --> 27:59.501
But he got his act together
pretty quickly.

27:59.501 --> 28:01.901
And Bailey will too.

28:03.200 --> 28:05.067
So as far as all this stuff
you told Claudia,

28:05.067 --> 28:07.200
maybe you have your own reasons
for believing it,

28:07.200 --> 28:09.067
but we don't need to hear it,
okay?

28:09.067 --> 28:12.567
You think I'm carrying out some
sort of old grudge against Nick?

28:12.567 --> 28:15.767
Everyone knows that
you were in love with her.

28:15.767 --> 28:17.968
So of course you're gonna
blow up every flaw he had.

28:17.968 --> 28:19.534
You didn't wanna believe
that he--

28:19.534 --> 28:20.667
That he belonged with her.

28:20.667 --> 28:22.300
That's not it.

28:22.300 --> 28:23.701
You're trying
to get back at him.

28:23.701 --> 28:26.133
That's not even close, Charlie.

28:26.133 --> 28:30.234
Because there's so much worse
I-- I could have told her.

28:32.067 --> 28:33.767
[SIGHS]

28:34.868 --> 28:36.801
[***]

28:38.300 --> 28:39.901
Bailey.

28:39.901 --> 28:43.834
Bailey, c-come on,
answer the door, please.

28:43.834 --> 28:45.667
Bailey!

28:45.667 --> 28:47.767
Bailey, talk to me, please.

28:51.267 --> 28:54.167
Callie, are you in there?

28:54.167 --> 28:55.100
Bailey!

28:56.434 --> 28:58.033
Oh, please be here.
Please be here.

28:58.033 --> 29:00.200
Please be here.

29:03.133 --> 29:04.400
[MUSIC OVER TV]

29:04.400 --> 29:07.667
* Down at the zoo
Down at the zoo *

29:07.667 --> 29:09.467
CHARLIE:
Hey.

29:09.467 --> 29:10.767
CLAUDIA:
Hey.

29:10.767 --> 29:12.234
Where you been?

29:12.234 --> 29:13.901
Nowhere.
I just had to do something.

29:13.901 --> 29:15.367
OWEN:
* Down at the zoo *

29:15.367 --> 29:17.901
I gotta get to the restaurant,
and I'm kinda late.

29:17.901 --> 29:18.968
Wanna come?

29:18.968 --> 29:21.234
To the restaurant?

29:21.234 --> 29:24.067
Yeah. Why not?
There's a TV there.

29:24.067 --> 29:26.801
You guys could help out in
the kitchen. It'll be fun.

29:26.801 --> 29:28.167
We're okay, Charlie.

29:28.167 --> 29:29.601
I can watch Owen.

29:29.601 --> 29:30.834
I know.

29:30.834 --> 29:33.300
I'm just saying I'd like
to have you there.

29:33.300 --> 29:35.100
I'd like us to be together.

29:35.100 --> 29:38.067
I-- I really--
I don't feel like it.

29:40.767 --> 29:43.200
If you're worried about Bailey,
he can find us there.

29:44.400 --> 29:46.367
I don't wanna go
to the restaurant.

29:46.367 --> 29:47.467
Why not?

29:47.467 --> 29:50.434
Because it's
his restaurant, Charlie.

29:50.434 --> 29:53.767
'Cause we're all yelling
at Bailey all the time

29:53.767 --> 29:56.601
and making it out like it--
It's all his fault or something.

29:56.601 --> 29:59.200
But it's not Bailey's fault,
Charlie. It's not.

29:59.200 --> 30:01.634
It's Dad's. It's Dad's fault.

30:01.634 --> 30:02.968
Claud, wait. Slow down.

30:02.968 --> 30:05.133
I don't wanna go
to his restaurant, Charlie,

30:05.133 --> 30:09.334
'cause then it's like
I forgive him, and I don't.

30:14.000 --> 30:14.934
[SIGHS]

30:22.801 --> 30:25.100
God, where have you been?
I've been looking for you.

30:26.467 --> 30:27.467
Bailey, wait.

30:27.467 --> 30:29.234
For what? Another lecture?

30:29.234 --> 30:30.167
Wait.

30:31.567 --> 30:33.901
Look, I know you feel like
you don't have any friends.

30:33.901 --> 30:35.968
Yeah. And I gotta say,
it's really growing on me.

30:35.968 --> 30:37.534
You're not gonna drive now,
are you?

30:37.534 --> 30:39.334
You've been drinking.
Get out of the way.

30:39.334 --> 30:40.634
No, Bailey. Let me drive. Okay?

30:40.634 --> 30:42.234
I'll take you
wherever you wanna go.

30:42.234 --> 30:43.234
A bar? I'll take you.

30:43.234 --> 30:44.167
No.
Bailey, stop it.

30:45.634 --> 30:47.601
Bailey, you can't do this.
You can't do this.

30:47.601 --> 30:49.334
Think about what you're doing.

30:49.334 --> 30:50.334
No, you can't do this!

30:50.334 --> 30:51.801
Get out of the car, Sarah.
No!

30:51.801 --> 30:53.334
Then shut up!

30:53.334 --> 30:54.968
[CAR STARTS]

30:56.968 --> 30:59.300
SARAH:
What's the matter with you?

30:59.300 --> 31:00.300
Bailey, stop the car.

31:00.300 --> 31:01.601
BAILEY:
I said, shut up.

31:01.601 --> 31:02.868
Take it easy. Be careful.

31:02.868 --> 31:04.033
Don't tell me how to drive!

31:04.033 --> 31:05.100
Bailey, look out!

31:05.100 --> 31:06.934
[HORN HONKS]
Look out!

31:08.734 --> 31:09.667
[SCREAMS]

31:20.868 --> 31:24.968
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
 <i>Dr. Indigo to the pharmacy.</i>
 <i>Dr. Indigo to the pharmacy.</i>

31:24.968 --> 31:26.334
Excuse me. Excuse me.

31:26.334 --> 31:27.767
Excuse me.
Where are you going?

31:27.767 --> 31:29.334
This is Sarah Reeves' room,
isn't it?

31:29.334 --> 31:31.834
Yes. Yes, it is. But I'm sorry.
You can't go in there.

31:31.834 --> 31:33.734
Her parents called me
and told me she's here.

31:33.734 --> 31:35.133
I just wanna make sure she's
okay.

31:35.133 --> 31:36.734
Only the immediate family's
allowed.

31:36.734 --> 31:39.501
No. No. See, please,
I'm-- I'm a friend.

31:39.501 --> 31:42.200
Please, just can't you at least
tell me if it's serious?

31:42.200 --> 31:43.734
She suffered
a few contusions,

31:43.734 --> 31:45.968
and she is under observation
for a concussion.

31:45.968 --> 31:47.534
Now, please--
What does that mean?

31:47.534 --> 31:49.067
I mean, how serious is that?

31:49.067 --> 31:51.767
Oh, she doesn't have any broken
bones, no internal injuries.

31:51.767 --> 31:53.067
She'll be going home tomorrow.

31:53.067 --> 31:55.267
Now, if you can wait over here,
you might get a chance

31:55.267 --> 31:57.267
to talk to her parents.
So she's gonna be okay?

31:57.267 --> 31:59.267
Yes.
[EXHALES]

32:02.334 --> 32:04.534
Wait. Wait.

32:04.534 --> 32:06.033
Where's Bailey?

32:07.100 --> 32:08.267
Bailey?
The driver.

32:08.267 --> 32:09.968
Where's the driver? Was--?
Was he hurt?

32:09.968 --> 32:11.434
I don't know. I never saw him.

32:11.434 --> 32:14.601
So you--?
So they just let him go?

32:14.601 --> 32:16.834
It wasn't my shift,
so I can't answer that.

32:16.834 --> 32:18.534
Well, somebody must have--

32:18.534 --> 32:20.767
I mean, isn't there anything
on her chart?

32:22.367 --> 32:24.067
Look, he's my brother.

32:25.400 --> 32:29.501
[INDISTINCT SPEECH OVER PA]

32:29.501 --> 32:31.300
Well, apparently,
he didn't leave a name.

32:31.300 --> 32:33.601
He just gave us her parents
number, and he left.

32:36.467 --> 32:38.400
[***]

32:41.234 --> 32:42.434
[SIGHS]

32:50.534 --> 32:52.501
[KEYS JINGLING]

33:00.267 --> 33:02.267
[CAR STARTS]

33:53.067 --> 33:54.000
Hey.

33:55.200 --> 33:56.467
What's out there?

33:59.467 --> 34:01.467
I'm not sure.
It's still pretty dark out.

34:06.567 --> 34:07.868
Is something on your mind?

34:08.801 --> 34:11.199
No, no.

34:11.199 --> 34:12.868
Not really. It's just...

34:15.234 --> 34:17.667
I guess I was just afraid
to fall asleep.

34:17.667 --> 34:19.801
Why?

34:19.801 --> 34:21.199
I don't know.

34:24.434 --> 34:27.234
You know, I was afraid
that maybe one of us

34:27.234 --> 34:30.000
was gonna suddenly wake up
and realize that last night

34:30.000 --> 34:31.967
was a big mistake.

34:32.833 --> 34:35.234
Like, say, you.

34:37.667 --> 34:39.766
Why would I do that?

34:39.766 --> 34:42.167
'Cause you've done it before.

34:44.467 --> 34:45.667
Griffin--

34:45.667 --> 34:47.868
Maybe because it's true.

34:49.234 --> 34:50.167
No.

34:51.199 --> 34:52.467
No, i-it's not.

34:52.467 --> 34:54.868
It wasn't a mistake.

34:57.200 --> 34:59.167
'Cause-- 'Cause now it's like

34:59.167 --> 35:01.634
we're together
in a different way.

35:01.634 --> 35:04.501
You know,
like really...

35:04.501 --> 35:07.167
 <i>together</i> together,
and I want that.

35:09.534 --> 35:10.934
Don't you?

35:12.434 --> 35:14.601
Yeah. Sure.

35:14.601 --> 35:20.133
And it-- It's weird,
but I didn't even know it

35:20.133 --> 35:22.534
until you got here.

35:22.534 --> 35:25.667
But when I first saw you
and...

35:25.667 --> 35:27.767
And when we were together...

35:28.734 --> 35:31.234
Last night, it's just...

35:32.501 --> 35:36.434
It was so what I need right now.

35:36.434 --> 35:39.200
It felt so great.

35:39.200 --> 35:44.167
I don't know, maybe that's why
I was that way at the lawyer's,

35:44.167 --> 35:47.434
but I-I really want things
to work out for us.

35:47.434 --> 35:50.367
I-I really don't want anything
to go wrong.

35:53.667 --> 35:55.834
It's not okay, Julia.

35:58.100 --> 36:00.067
I don't want it to be like that.

36:02.601 --> 36:08.067
You-- Y-you can't second-guess
everything that I do.

36:08.067 --> 36:10.367
You know, y-y-you gotta
trust me once in a while.

36:10.367 --> 36:11.534
I know.

36:11.534 --> 36:13.968
I know, and I'm sorry.

36:16.367 --> 36:18.868
But-- But I want you
to understand that if I--

36:18.868 --> 36:20.067
If I push you--

36:20.067 --> 36:21.567
And I know
that I shouldn't.

36:21.567 --> 36:24.100
But if I do,
it's just...

36:27.033 --> 36:30.033
Whatever you're gonna do,
Griffin, like,

36:30.033 --> 36:34.167
wherever you're gonna go,
we're going together.

36:36.868 --> 36:37.801
[SIGHS]

36:45.267 --> 36:47.000
Morning.

36:49.234 --> 36:51.200
Where have you been?

36:52.334 --> 36:53.868
What's the matter?

36:53.868 --> 36:56.467
You can't just disappear like
that, Julia, especially now,

36:56.467 --> 36:58.067
especially with all this--
What?

36:58.067 --> 36:59.834
What are you talking about?

36:59.834 --> 37:00.934
[SIGHS]

37:06.634 --> 37:08.400
Bailey had an accident.

37:08.400 --> 37:09.934
What?

37:09.934 --> 37:12.200
Sarah was in the car,
and she got hurt.

37:12.200 --> 37:14.167
Oh, my God.
She's in the hospital.

37:14.167 --> 37:18.801
They're watching her for
some concussion or whatever.

37:18.801 --> 37:20.467
I mean, she's gonna be okay,
but--

37:20.467 --> 37:23.300
Where's Bailey?
Charlie, is he--?

37:23.300 --> 37:25.501
I don't know. He disappeared.

37:25.501 --> 37:28.567
He drove Sarah to the hospital,
and then he disappeared.

37:28.567 --> 37:30.601
All right. So-- So he must be--

37:30.601 --> 37:34.133
I mean, i-if he drove her there,
then he must be okay.

37:34.133 --> 37:36.701
I don't know.

37:36.701 --> 37:38.968
I don't know.

37:38.968 --> 37:40.901
Charlie, it's gotta be okay.

37:40.901 --> 37:42.567
I mean, he's gotta
be sobered up by now.

37:42.567 --> 37:45.100
It's not okay, Julia.

37:45.100 --> 37:47.601
It's not even close to okay.

37:48.667 --> 37:50.767
[SIGHS]

37:50.767 --> 37:54.267
I thought I knew what
I was doing, you know?

37:54.267 --> 37:58.100
I thought I could just
draw some line with him.

37:58.100 --> 37:59.667
Then maybe it would
hurt us a little,

37:59.667 --> 38:01.100
but mostly,
it would hurt him.

38:01.100 --> 38:03.300
And he'd have to come around.

38:03.300 --> 38:05.367
[SIGHS, SNIFFLES]

38:06.467 --> 38:08.367
But I was wrong, Jule.

38:09.701 --> 38:12.968
There's other people
involved here.

38:12.968 --> 38:14.334
[SIGHS]

38:14.334 --> 38:15.467
I mean, Owen.

38:16.767 --> 38:20.834
And Sarah, she--
She almost got killed.

38:20.834 --> 38:23.067
I-- I almost got her killed.

38:23.067 --> 38:25.300
CLAUDIA:
It's not your fault, Charlie.

38:25.300 --> 38:27.367
It's nobody's fault but Dad's.

38:27.367 --> 38:29.868
I mean, this whole thing--
Would you cut it out with that?

38:29.868 --> 38:31.200
It's not helping, Claud!

38:31.200 --> 38:33.100
You're not helping anybody,
okay?!

38:40.267 --> 38:41.868
[DOOR SLAMS]

38:46.067 --> 38:47.534
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

38:52.534 --> 38:54.367
[DOOR CLOSES]

38:58.834 --> 39:00.167
[SIGHS]

39:02.434 --> 39:03.801
I'm sorry, Claud.

39:07.501 --> 39:09.634
I shouldn't have
yelled at you.

39:14.701 --> 39:17.634
But I don't get it.

39:17.634 --> 39:20.100
I don't get why
you're so mad at him.

39:20.100 --> 39:23.400
Because of what
he did to us.

39:23.400 --> 39:27.300
But what did he do to you,
really?

39:28.534 --> 39:30.868
Because he didn't
make Bailey drink.

39:30.868 --> 39:32.067
I know you think he did, but--

39:32.067 --> 39:34.267
Yes, he did. I mean,
he gave him this problem.

39:34.267 --> 39:35.934
No, Claud.

39:35.934 --> 39:38.501
Even if Bailey did get
the alcoholism from him,

39:38.501 --> 39:41.267
Dad couldn't help that
any more than--

39:41.267 --> 39:43.701
Than Mom could help
giving you her music.

39:43.701 --> 39:46.434
Maybe not,

39:46.434 --> 39:49.868
but he could help
what he did to her.

39:49.868 --> 39:53.067
He could help being
a bad husband and a bad father.

39:53.067 --> 39:55.968
He wasn't, Claud.

39:55.968 --> 39:59.000
He quit drinking.
He made himself better.

39:59.000 --> 40:02.400
And-- And the guy he was
after that, you loved him.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.100
You thought he was
a great father.

40:04.100 --> 40:06.067
I don't care.
I don't think that anymore.

40:07.968 --> 40:11.501
You know, I've made
a lot of mistakes too,

40:13.501 --> 40:15.000
stuff that's hurt this family.

40:16.734 --> 40:19.834
And I tell myself

40:19.834 --> 40:23.400
that you need to screw up
before you can learn.

40:23.400 --> 40:26.367
You know, like, maybe
you gotta be a lousy person

40:26.367 --> 40:29.801
before you can be a good one.

40:29.801 --> 40:33.067
But Owen, I mean...

40:35.300 --> 40:39.033
What if someday Owen looks at me
the way you're looking at Dad?

40:39.033 --> 40:41.901
'Cause if he does,
there's no reason why

40:41.901 --> 40:43.701
he won't decide to hate me.

40:46.334 --> 40:48.334
You're different, Charlie.

40:48.334 --> 40:51.067
The stuff you did, it's--

40:51.067 --> 40:52.634
It's just not the same thing.

40:52.634 --> 40:55.100
Yes, it is.

40:55.100 --> 40:57.734
It's exactly the same.

41:01.467 --> 41:04.901
He was a good father, Claud.

41:04.901 --> 41:08.000
And if he was still around,
he'd be a good father now.

41:10.167 --> 41:12.567
[SIGHS]

41:12.567 --> 41:14.434
Claudia...

